      "content": {
        "title": "Dupuytren Disease and Hand Contractures — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Fibroproliferative disorder of palmar fascia and other contractures including Volkmann ischemic contracture and intrinsic tightness.",
        "summary": "Dupuytren cords cause MCP and PIP contracture; collagenase and fasciectomy are treatment options. Volkmann contracture follows compartment syndrome."
      },
